# Cross-validation
cv_results <- MASS::lda(birthMonth ~ ., data=bdata[, c(3:15)], CV=TRUE)
## Warning in lda.default(x, grouping, ...): variables are collinear
cv_results$cv
## NULL
  1. RESIDUAL ANALYSIS
# Residuals
residuals <- cv_results$posterior[,2] - as.numeric(bdata$birthMonth == "True")
## Warning in cv_results$posterior[, 2] - as.numeric(bdata$birthMonth == "True"):
## longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
# Histogram of residuals
hist(residuals, breaks=20, col="skyblue", main="Histogram of Residuals", xlab="Residuals")

# Diagnostic plots
plot(discriminant_model)

factor_cols <- sapply(bdata, is.factor)
for (col in names(bdata)[factor_cols]) {
  if (length(levels(bdata[[col]])) < 2) {
    # Convert the factor variable to character
    bdata[[col]] <- as.character(bdata[[col]])
    # Check unique values and convert back to factor with appropriate levels
    new_levels <- unique(new_data[[col]])
    bdata[[col]] <- factor(bdata[[col]], levels = new_levels)
  }
}
